  "text": "Proof. See Appendix B. Remark 5.15. Note carefully that we do not consider a change of coordinates that produces a linear dynamical system, i.e., we do not assume F is linear in Lemma 5.14. In general, such a change of coordinates does exist near a hyperbolic fixed point by the Hartman-Grobman theorem (see, e.g., Theorem 10.4 of [CITATION_1] ), but it is only guaranteed to be a homeomorphism (not necessarily Lipschitz). We need the change of coordinates to be Lipschitz in order to compare distances up to a constant.",
